git config: used to identify the user to make sure that the person pushing into the repo 
to use:
git config --global user.email "user email"
git config --global user.name "user name"

git init: used to create a new repo
to use: 
git init "the name of the new repo"
git merge: used to add the new changes we made in the copy and merge it with the origin, if the owner wanted the merge to happen.
to use:
git merge "branch"
git remote:  used to responsible for syncing changes and let's you create connections to other repos
to use: 
git remote
